{"title":"Beyond Cuteness: An Emerging Field of the Psychology of “Kawaii”","link":"https://iafor.org/beyond-cuteness-an-emerging-field-of-the-psychology-of-kawaii/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=beyond-cuteness-an-emerging-field-of-the-psychology-of-kawaii","date":1567739788000,"content":"<p><img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"The Psychology of Kawaii Professor Hiroshi Nittono Osaka University\" srcset=\"https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-150x150.jpg 150w, https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-600x600.jpg 600w, https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-100x100.jpg 100w, https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-50x50.jpg 50w, https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-300x300.jpg 300w, https://iafor.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Psychology-of-Kawaii-Professor-Hiroshi-Nittono-Osaka-University-32x32.jpg 32w\" />“Kawaii” is often translated as “cute” in English, but the nuances and connotations of the two words seem to be different. In this presentation, Professor Hiroshi Nittono of Osaka University discusses which aspects of kawaii are unique to Japanese culture and which aspects seem to be universal to all humans.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://iafor.org/beyond-cuteness-an-emerging-field-of-the-psychology-of-kawaii/\">Beyond Cuteness: An Emerging Field of the Psychology of “Kawaii”</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://iafor.org\">The International Academic Forum (IAFOR)</a>.</p>","author":"IAFOR","siteTitle":"The International Academic Forum (IAFOR)"